Primaries for the State House of Assembly by the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) began today Sunday some hours ago with a charge by the Chairman, Abia House of Assembly Constituency Electoral Committee, Rt Hon Erim Ubom, warning that any Constituency whose result does not meet the electoral guidelines as contained in the Electoral Act as well as the PDP constitution will be penalized with the result cancelled. The three-man adhoc delegates are drawn from the INEC Electoral Wards of the 17 LGAs of Abia State. They were joined by a one-man delegate from the LGAs. Both the State House of Assembly and House of Representatives of PDP Primaries are being held today. However, the one for the State House of Assembly is starting six hours behind schedule. -Advertisement- There are fears that that the one for the House of Representatives may hold very late and may likely spill over to Monday morning because of the late commencement of the House of Assembly Primary. In an interview, Irem Ubom, disclosed that his Committee will conduct a free, fair and credible primary, pointing out that any adhoc Committee that returns result that does not comply with the PDP guidelines will be sanctioned and the result rejected. Details comingâ€¦